comments: Anderson's (MIN) hand comes down and initiates contact to Achiuwa's (TOR) head/face, which affects his driving shot attempt. The illegal contact occurs prior to Gobert's (MIN) contact with the ball.
Gobert (MIN) exits the paint within three seconds.
Gobert (MIN) legally contests Siakam's (TOR) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Achiuwa (TOR) brings his arm toward Edwards' (MIN) path and brushes Edwards' front during the drive. The contact that occurs is marginal.
Anunoby (TOR) cleanly blocks Edwards' (MIN) driving shot attempt.
Edwards (MIN) avoids making contact with Schroder's (TOR) arm as he defends him near midcourt.
Barnes (TOR) establishes himself in Edwards' (MIN) path and does not deliver illegal contact during the pick.
Anunoby (TOR) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Anderson's (MIN) arm after the release.
As Conley (MIN) moves around the pick, marginal contact occurs with Schroder's (TOR) front during his drive.
Achiuwa (TOR) establishes himself in Conley's (MIN) path and firms up over his right foot to absorb the marginal upper body contact that occurs as the pick is set.
Conley (MIN) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Schroder's (TOR) arm after the release.
Anunoby (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects it away from Gobert (MIN) during the post entry pass.
Gobert (MIN) firms up over his left foot in Anunoby's (TOR) path and he absorbs the marginal contact during the screen.
Edwards (MIN) gathers the pass on his right foot and takes two steps before entering his upward shooting motion.
Towns (MIN) and Siakam (TOR) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
The ball deflects off of Anunoby's (TOR) foot and goes out of bounds.
Schroder (TOR) legally contests Conley's (MIN) jump shot attempt.
Achiuwa (TOR) and Gobert (MIN) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Schroder (TOR) contests the jump shot attempt and does not initiate the marginal contact that occurs as he lands in front of Towns (MIN).
Towns (MIN) returns both feet to the floor and he does not overtly kick out or extend into Schroder (TOR) following the release of his jump shot attempt.
